@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
                               @{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}What Is BigTime@{ub}

You've no doubt seen modular screen blankers till the're coming out of your
ears, well fret not the first modular clock has arrived!

BigTime @{fg highlight}SHOULD@{fg text} work on any Amiga with WorkBench 2 or higher.

@{"The Big Picture" alink "Bin/Misc/BigTime.Demo.IFF/main" 0}

@endnode

@node "Main Preferences" "Main Preferences"
                             @{b}@{u}Main Preferences@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}BigTime Commodity@{ub}
BigTime installs itself as a commodity, if you try to run it twice the  second
attempt will fail and cause the first to bring up its interface.

The default hotkey for BigTime is <@{b}lalt control t@{ub}>.

If you tell the BigTime commodity to be disabled, all the open clock faces will close
until you enable it again.

@{b}BigTime Interface@{ub}

@{b}CLI Args@{ub}
All CLI args will override tooltypes.

    @{i}          CLOCK@{ui}:-    Specify clock names to launch, this is case
sensitive so care must be taken, to specify more than one clock you must enclose
in " "'s i.e. "TitleBar Text".
    @{i}       UPDATE/N@{ui}:-    The interval in seconds between clock time updates.
    @{i}    CX_POPKEY/K@{ui}:-    Key to cause interface to popup.
    @{i}   CX_POPUP/S/K@{ui}:-    Popup interface when run.
    @{i}CX_PRIORITY/N/K@{ui}:-    Commodity priority.

@{b}ToolTypes@{ub}
    @{i}      UNITDIR@{ui}:-    Path to "Unit" directory.
    @{i}BEVELBOXFILLS@{ui}:-    Fill bevelboxes.
    @{i}GADGETBORDERS@{ui}:-    Draw black border around gadgets.
    @{i}       UPDATE@{ui}:-    The interval in seconds between clock time updates.
    @{i}         NAME@{ui}:-    User name.
    @{i}         PASS@{ui}:-    User pass.

    @{i}   CX_POPUP@{ui}:-      Popup interface when run.
    @{i}  CX_POPKEY@{ui}:-      Key to cause interface to popup.
    @{i}CX_PRIORITY@{ui}:-      Commodity priority.

@{b}Menus@{ub}
    @{i}About@{ui}:-     Version/Reg/Author details
    @{i} Quit@{ui}:-     Quit BigTime Application

@{b}The Rest@{ub}
    @{i}Clock Faces@{ui}:-   Clicking on an entry will either launch the clock or
                             terminate it, depending on it's current state.
    @{i}Preferences@{ui}:-   Causes selected clock to open it prefs window.
      @{i}Update(S)@{ui}:-   The interval in seconds between clock time updates.

           @{i}Hide@{ui}:-   Hides the clock face and all related windows for 5
                             seconds.
           @{i}Save@{ui}:-   Save preferences to BigTime Icon.

@{i}Alarms - Chimes@{ui}:-   This listview contains the current setup of alarms and
                    chimes, these are sorted in order of imminence, if a
                    non-repeating event has been triggered, selecting it
                    will reactivate it.
            @{i}New@{ui}:-   This will create a new event, if one was selected
                    before the button was pressed the new event will be a
                    copy of it.
         @{i}Delete@{ui}:-   Delete currently selected event.
         @{i}Repeat@{ui}:-   Cause the event to repeat itself.
           @{i}Type@{ui}:-   Set the type of event either Alarm or Chime.
         @{i}Minute@{ui}:-   Set the minute at which event will occur.
           @{i}Hour@{ui}:-   If the checkbox is set then the hour at which the
                    event will occur can be specified.
            @{i}Day@{ui}:-   If the checkbox is set then the day at which the
                    event will occur can be specified.

@{b}Example settings for Events@{ub}
@{bg highlight}D:--- H:-- M:00 C R   @{bg back}  Chime every hour of every day.

@{bg highlight}D:Mon H:20 M:55 A R   @{bg back}  Trigger Alarm on every Monday at 5 minutes to 9.

@{bg highlight}D:Tue H:09 M:00 A     @{bg back}  Trigger Alarm at 9 O'clock on Tuesday.

@{bg highlight}D:Wed H:08 M:00 A   U @{bg back}  An Alarm which has been trigger and is no longer
                        active.

@{bg highlight}D:--- H:09 M:00 A R   @{bg back}  Trigger Alarm at 9 O'clock every day.
@endnode

@node "Testing, Revision Info" "Testing, Revision Info"
                          @{b}@{u}Testing, Revision Info@{ub}@{uu}

This software has been tested on the following:-
        A1200  6Mb 410Mb 88020   68882
        A4000 10Mb ???Mb 68030EC 68882
        A1000  5Mb ???Mb 68030   68882

@{b}Revision Info@{ub}
@{fg highlight}V1.0@{fg text} ---- 6/8/1995 ---- First release No known bugs!
@{fg highlight}V1.1@{fg text} ---- 7/1/1996 ---- Bug in Dialog.Unit caused
        crashes when changing font in Scale and Calender ClockFaces.
@{fg highlight}V1.2@{fg text} ---- 2/6/1996 ---- Bug in Dialog.Unit caused
        memory loss.
        DEFCHIMEPATH and DEFALARMPATH added.
        Cookie clockface added.

@{fg highlight}V2.0@{fg text} ---- 30/6/1996 ---- Rewrite!
        Multiple clocks can be launched simultaneously.
        Alarm/Chime events moved to their own module.
        Modules updated.
        Slight change to some interfaces.
        Some bugs fixed.
        ChipAudio.Unit superceeded by Audio.Unit, this allows samples larger
than 128K to be played, also if sample is to big to fit in the largest chunk
of free memory(FAST or CHIP) the unit will play the sample from disk.
        Selection of clocks from CLI added, slight changes to CLI arg spec.

@endnode

@node "ShareWare Details" "ShareWare Details"
                             @{b}@{u}ShareWare Details@{ub}@{uu}

The software you are using is unregistered, because of this the application
will automatically quit itself after @{fg highlight}10 minutes@{fg text}.

To register send me @{b}5 English pounds@{ub}, or a cheque for the same amount, and a
@{b}SAE@{ub}, I will in return send you a PASS and a NAME which when saved as tooltypes
in the BigTime's icon will remove the 10 minute restriction.

If you have an email account include your address and if I can I'll email you
the information instead of snail-mailing it. (Still enclose an @{b}SAE@{ub} just  in
case I can't email you)

Depending on whether anyone registers and how much time I have free I'll
continue writting more modules (Hour Glass, Candle, Sun Dial, Cuckoo Clock
etc.)

See @{"AuthorĀInfo" link "About the Author" 0} for address.
@endnode

