@node "Analogue" "Analogue"
                             @{b}@{u}Analogue ClockModule@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}Description@{ub}
The Analogue clock opens a sizeable window in which a analogue clock is
rendered, the markers for hours and minutes can be turn off as can the
second's hand.  The background of the clock can either be set to a single
colour or an IFF image can be render there, the image can be centered or
tiled, the image colours will be remaped.

@{b}Preferences@{ub}
  Second Hand:   If selected then a seconds hand will be displayed.
      Colours:   Allows the colour of the selected item to be changed via
                 the palette gadget on the left of it.
   Show Ticks:   This specifies whether the markers for minutes and hours
                 are rendered.
    Wallpaper:   This allows the background of the clock to be changed,
                 Solid will render the background in the specified colour,
                 Tile will load the selected image and tile the background
                 with it, Image will also load an image but it will center
                 it in the middle of the clock.( Some patterns are stored
                 in "BigTime/Bin/Analogue/" for you to try.
                 @{"SkullTile" alink "Bin/Analogue/SkullTile.iff/main" 0}  @{"GraveTile" alink "Bin/Analogue/GraveTile.iff/main" 0}  @{"FishTile" alink "Bin/Analogue/FishTile.iff/main" 0}  @{"FujiTile" alink "Bin/Analogue/FujiTile.iff/main" 0}  @{"Green
allTile" alink "Bin/Analogue/GreenBallTile.iff/main" 0}
                 @{"PinkBallTile" alink "Bin/Analogue/PinkBallTile.iff/main" 0}  @{"MeshTile" alink "Bin/Analogue/MeshTile.iff/main" 0}  @{"ScaleTile" alink "Bin/Analogue/ScaleTile.iff/main" 0}  @{"WaveTile" alink "Bin/Analogue/WaveTile.iff/main" 0}  @{
Skull2Tile" alink "Bin/Analogue/Skull2Tile.iff/main" 0}
     IFF Path:   This specifies the image to be used when Wallpaper is in
                 Tile or Image mode.
         Save:   Save preferences to icon's tooltypes.

@{b}Revision Info@{ub}
@{fg highlight}V1.0@{fg text} ---- 28/8/1995 ---- First release No known bugs!
@{fg highlight}V2.0@{fg text} ---- 30/7/1996 ---- Alterations for V2.0
@endnode

@node "AppIcon" "AppIcon"
                            @{b}@{u}AppIcon ClockModule@{ub}@{uu}
@{b}Description@{ub}
This module creates a AppIcon with the current time rendered on it, the
current date is shown by the AppIcons title, due to the way AppIcons are
implemented when the time updates the AppIcon is removed and then added
back, this will cause a flickering if you have a quick update and you are
in a mode that displays seconds.

@{b}Preferences@{ub}
  Default Pos:   If checked then LeftEdge and TopEdge will be ignored.
     LeftEdge:   Sets the position of the left edge of the Icon.
      TopEdge:   Sets the position of the top edge of the Icon.
     OffSet X:   Adds this value to the left and right border of the Icon.
     OffSet Y:   Adds this value to the top and bottom border of the Icon.
  Time Format:   Allows time format of clock to be selected.
         Save:   Save preferences to icon's tooltypes.

@{b}Revision Info@{ub}
@{fg highlight}V1.0@{fg text} ---- 28/8/1995 ---- First release No known bugs!
@{fg highlight}V2.0@{fg text} ---- 30/7/1996 ---- Alterations for V2.0
@endnode

@node "AppItem" "AppItem"
                            @{b}@{u}AppItem ClockModule@{ub}@{uu}
@{b}Description@{ub}
This module creates an AppMenuItem showing the current time.

@{b}Usage@{ub}
If you select this MenuItem it will change to the current date for 5
seconds, this function will not work if your Time Update is less than 5
seconds and your TimeFormat is in a mode that displays seconds.

@{b}Preferences@{ub}
  Time Format:   Allows time format of clock to be selected.
         Save:   Save preferences to icon's tooltypes.

@{b}Revision Info@{ub}
@{fg highlight}V1.0@{fg text} ---- 28/8/1995 ---- First release No known bugs!
@{fg highlight}V2.0@{fg text} ---- 30/7/1996 ---- Alterations for V2.0
@endnode

@node "Calender" "Calender"
                           @{b}@{u}Calender ClockModule@{ub}@{uu}
@{b}Description@{ub}
The Calender clock module opens a window with the calender for the current
month in it, the current day is highlighted and the font used can be
changed.

@{b}Preferences@{ub}
  Time Format:   Allows time format of clock to be selected.
  Select Font:   Allows font and font pens to be selected.
         Save:   Save preferences to icon's tooltypes.

@{b}Revision Info@{ub}
@{fg highlight}V1.0@{fg text} ---- 4/1/1996 ---- First release No known bugs!?
@{fg highlight}V1.1@{fg text} ---- 7/1/1996 ---- Slight change to interface.
@{fg highlight}V2.0@{fg text} ---- 30/7/1996 ---- Alterations for V2.0
@endnode

