@node "Cookie" "Cookie"
                            @{b}@{u}Cookie ClockModule@{ub}@{uu}
@{b}Description@{ub}
This clock module displays random cookies when an alarm or chime event
happens, you can also force it to show a new one by activating the window
and pressing any key.

The Cookie window can be shrunk by clicking on the zoom gadget.

@{b}Format of CookieList@{ub}

This file contains all the cookies, cookies are separated by Carriage
Returns(1 or more), comments can also be inserted, these are distinguished
by a preceeding  semi-colon (";"). If a carriage return is desired in the
output use "@" to signify this. Look at the CookieList file for examples.

A single cookie can be of any length as long as it is all on one line.

Cookie will automatically generate a file, containing hash offsets into
the CookieList if one does not exist, it will also update it if the List
changes.

@{b}Preferences@{ub}
      Time Format:   Allows time format of clock to be selected.
            Width:   Width in characters of ListView.(Used to display cookie).
           Height:   Height in characters of ListView.(Used to display cookie).
      Chime PopUp:   Expand window and select new cookie on chime.
      Alarm PopUp:   Expand window and select new cookie on alarm.
Number Of Cookies:   Number of cookies in current cookie list.
        List Path:   Path to cookie list.
             Save:   Save preferences to icon's tooltypes.

@{b}Revision Info@{ub}
@{fg highlight}V1.0@{fg text} ---- 4/1/1996 ---- First release No known bugs!?
@{fg highlight}V2.0@{fg text} ---- 30/7/1996 ---- Alterations for V2.0
@endnode

@node "Event" "Event"
                            @{b}@{u}Event ClockModule@{ub}@{uu}
@{b}Description@{ub}
This module handles the notification to the user of a chime or alarm event,
the user can specify which of four events should be triggered when the
chime/alarm is recieved.


@{b}Preferences@{ub}
 Display Beep :   Cause intuition to alert the user.
    Requester :   Bring up a requester informing the user of the event.
      Execute :   Execute a command.
        Audio :   Play an audio sample (IFF/RAW).
         Save :   Save preferences to icon's tooltypes.

@{b}Revision Info@{ub}
@{fg highlight}V2.0@{fg text} ---- 30/7/1996 ---- First release
@endnode

@node "Moon" "Moon"
                             @{b}@{u}Moon ClockModule@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}Description@{ub}
The Moon clock opens a window with a remaped image of the moon in it, this
image is altered to show it's current phase.  The current time is rendered
in the windows title bar.

@{b}Usage@{ub}
By clicking in the window the current date will be shown in the windows
title bar and various information on the moon will be render in the screen
title bar.

@{b}Preferences@{ub}
  Time Format:   Allows time format of clock to be selected.
         Save:   Save preferences to icon's tooltypes.

@{b}Revision Info@{ub}
@{fg highlight}V1.0@{fg text} ---- 28/8/1995 ---- First release No known bugs!
@{fg highlight}V2.0@{fg text} ---- 30/7/1996 ---- Alterations for V2.0
@endnode

