@node "Scale" "Scale"
                             @{b}@{u}Scale ClockModule@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}Description@{ub}
The Scale clock opens a sizeable window in which the current time is
rendered, the font size is altered to fit the window.

@{b}Preferences@{ub}
  Time Format:   Allows time format of clock to be selected.
  Select Font:   Allows font and font pens to be selected.
         Save:   Save preferences to icon's tooltypes.

@{b}Revision Info@{ub}
@{fg highlight}V1.0@{fg text} ---- 28/8/1995 ---- First release No known bugs!
@{fg highlight}V2.0@{fg text} ---- 30/6/1996 ---- Alterations for V2.0
@endnode

@node "Schedule" "Schedule"
                            @{b}@{u}Schedule ClockModule@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}Description@{ub}
The Schedule module allows you to select a date and some associated text, this
text will be displayed in a requester when the current time is beyond the events
time, if the current time is more than a day ahead of the events time then the
event will be considered expired.

An expired event is signified by the day display showing "---".

@{b}Preferences@{ub}
    Schedule List:   List of events.
              New:   Create new event, if already selected event, then copy it.
           Delete:   Delete event.
             Year:   Set year 1979-2087.
            Month:   Set month.
              Day:   Set day of month.
             Time:   Set time.
Event Description:   The text to be displayed.
             Save:   Save preferences to icon's tooltypes.

@{b}Revision Info@{ub}
@{fg highlight}V2.0@{fg text} ---- 21/7/1996 ---- Alterations for V2.0
@endnode

@node "Text" "Text"
                             @{b}@{u}Text ClockModule@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}Description@{ub}
This clock module opens a window consisting of only a titlebar,
inside the titlebar the current time is rendered in English.

@{b}Usage@{ub}
Click on the clock to cause it to show the date for 5 seconds.

@{b}Preferences@{ub}
   Lock Width:   Lock the titlebar to it's maximum size.
      Shift X:   Shift the titlebar horizontally when it's width changes.
         Save:   Save preferences to icon's tooltypes.

@{b}Revision Info@{ub}
@{fg highlight}V1.0@{fg text} ---- 28/8/1995 ---- First release No known bugs!
@{fg highlight}V2.0@{fg text} ---- 30/7/1996 ---- Alterations for V2.0
@endnode

@node "TitleBar" "TitleBar"
                           @{b}@{u}TitleBar ClockModule@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}Description@{ub}
This module places a digital clock in the top right of your screens
titlebar, the clock will automagically select fore and background
pens.  The clock will also handle proportional fonts correctly.

@{b}Usage@{ub}
Click on the clock to cause it to show the date for 5 seconds.

@{b}Preferences@{ub}
  Time Format:   Allows time format of clock to be selected.
         Save:   Save preferences to icon's tooltypes.

@{b}Revision Info@{ub}
@{fg highlight}V1.0@{fg text} ---- 2/9/1995 ---- First release No known bugs!
@{fg highlight}V2.0@{fg text} ---- 30/7/1996 ---- Alterations for V2.0
@endnode

@node "User" "User"
                              @{b}@{u}User ClockModule@{ub}@{uu}
@{b}Description@{ub}
This module allows you to create your own clockface, the template source
code for a your own clock is located in Bigtime/bin/user/.
When this module is run it will launch your clock program and then send
messages to it via the specified port name. If at anytime it cannot find
your port it will assume that your module has terminated.
This module can be copied and renamed (i.e. more than one copy in the
clockface dir) this allows more than one user clock to be written.

@{b}Preferences@{ub}
    User Port:   Name of your public message port.
    User Path:   Path to your clock module.
       Launch:   Launch your clock module.
    Terminate:   Send a Mesage to your module telling it to quit.
        Prefs:   Send a Mesage to your module telling it to display it's
                 preferences window.( if any )
         Save:   Save preferences to icon's tooltypes.

@{b}Revision Info@{ub}
@{fg highlight}V1.0@{fg text} ---- 28/8/1995 ---- First release No known bugs!
@{fg highlight}V2.0@{fg text} ---- 30/7/1996 ---- Alterations for V2.0
@endnode
